    <section class="phases">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Step by step</h2>
        <span class="hint">18 phases · 36 messages · three contracts joined by <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:13px;color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-2);padding:1px 6px;border-radius:5px;">linkedContractId</code></span>
      </div>

      <div class="phase-grid">

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">1</span>
          <span class="tag">Catalog</span>
          <h3>Three BPPs publish</h3>
          <p>Toko Elektronik publishes its product catalog with policy IRIs. GoPay publishes its payment methods and MDR schedule. JNE publishes rate logic and provincial coverage. Pasar Sapa keeps a fresh local index.</p>
          <ul><li>/catalog/publish ×3</li><li>/on_subscribe</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase user">
          <span class="num">2</span>
          <span class="tag">Browse</span>
          <h3>Andi opens the app</h3>
          <p>Search runs against Pasar Sapa's local index — no live network call. The listing surfaces with its declared <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">availability.status</code>.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">3</span>
          <span class="tag">Trade · select</span>
          <h3>Quote the order</h3>
          <p>BAP submits item, qty, drop pincode. BPP returns a quote with structured breakup including PPN at the rate sourced from current PMK.</p>
          <ul><li>/select</li><li>/on_select</li><li>quote.breakup</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">4</span>
          <span class="tag">Trade · init</span>
          <h3>Address + payment intent</h3>
          <p>BAP commits the consumer's full Surabaya address. Crucially, the BPP's <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">/on_init</code> returns a <b>paymentRequest</b> — amount, payee VPA, idempotency key — to be discharged via the Payment sector.</p>
          <ul><li>/init</li><li>/on_init</li><li>paymentRequest</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase pay">
          <span class="num">5</span>
          <span class="tag">Payment · select</span>
          <h3>Discover methods</h3>
          <p>BAP queries the Payment BPP with the amount and parties. GoPay returns supported methods (QRIS, VA, EWALLET) with the MDR for each — letting the BAP show price-by-method to the consumer.</p>
          <ul><li>/select</li><li>/on_select</li><li>methods</li><li>MDR</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase pay">
          <span class="num">6</span>
          <span class="tag">Payment · init</span>
          <h3>Get the instrument</h3>
          <p>Consumer picks QRIS. BAP <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--pay);">/init</code>s the chosen method; GoPay returns the QRIS string with an expiry and a <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--pay);">paymentRef</code>.</p>
          <ul><li>/init</li><li>/on_init</li><li>qrisString</li><li>expiresAt</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase pay">
          <span class="num">7</span>
          <span class="tag">Payment · confirm + status</span>
          <h3>Authorize, then PAID</h3>
          <p>BAP confirms with <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--accent);">linkedContractId</code> pointing at the Trade contract. Andi scans the QR in his GoPay app — the actual money rides BI-FAST off-network. GoPay then pushes <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--status);">/on_status [PAID]</code> with <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">settlementId</code> and <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">NTPN</code>.</p>
          <ul><li>/confirm</li><li>/on_confirm</li><li>/on_status</li><li>NTPN</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">8</span>
          <span class="tag">Trade · confirm</span>
          <h3>Bind the Trade contract</h3>
          <p>Now that payment is verifiable on-network, BAP confirms with the merchant and attaches <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--pay);">paymentReference</code>. Toko Elektronik (PKP) returns Faktur Pajak ref + fulfilment warehouse. <b>Trade contract ACTIVE</b>.</p>
          <ul><li>/confirm</li><li>/on_confirm</li><li>paymentReference</li><li>fakturPajakReference</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase logi">
          <span class="num">9</span>
          <span class="tag">Logistics · select</span>
          <h3>Bind a binding rate</h3>
          <p>BAP calls JNE with the actual shipment profile — pickup, drop, weight, declared value. JNE returns a binding rate with a quote validity window.</p>
          <ul><li>/select</li><li>/on_select</li><li>quoteValidityWindow</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase logi">
          <span class="num">10</span>
          <span class="tag">Logistics · init</span>
          <h3>Apply Framework Agreement</h3>
          <p>BAP attaches the active <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--logi);">logistics-fwa</code> reference (Pasar Sapa × JNE 2026 Q2). The FWA's commercial envelope supersedes per-offer policies.</p>
          <ul><li>/init</li><li>/on_init</li><li>fwaReference</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase logi">
          <span class="num">11</span>
          <span class="tag">Logistics · confirm</span>
          <h3>The third linked contract</h3>
          <p>Logistics confirm carries <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--accent);">linkedContractId</code> pointing at the Trade contract. JNE returns an AWB; the Logistics contract is ACTIVE.</p>
          <ul><li>/confirm</li><li>/on_confirm</li><li>linkedContractId</li><li>awbNumber</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">12</span>
          <span class="tag">Status</span>
          <h3>DISPATCHED + PICKED_UP</h3>
          <p>BPP-Trade pushes <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">DISPATCHED</code> with the AWB. JNE collects from the merchant warehouse and pushes <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">PICKED_UP</code> — proxy phone numbers only.</p>
          <ul><li>/on_status</li><li>awbNumber</li><li>phoneProxy</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase logi">
          <span class="num">13</span>
          <span class="tag">Logistics · transit</span>
          <h3>Hub routing + live track</h3>
          <p>JNE moves the parcel through its Jakarta hub (P2H2P). BAP opens a <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--logi);">/track</code> session for live GPS, in addition to coarse status pushes.</p>
          <ul><li>/track</li><li>/on_track</li><li>IN_TRANSIT</li><li>OUT_FOR_DELIVERY</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">14</span>
          <span class="tag">Delivered</span>
          <h3>Both contracts close</h3>
          <p>JNE pushes <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--status);">DELIVERED</code> with a delivery-proof photo. BAP relays via <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">/update</code>; Trade contract → COMPLETE. Andi gets a push.</p>
          <ul><li>/on_status</li><li>deliveryProofUrl</li><li>contract → COMPLETE</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase user">
          <span class="num">15</span>
          <span class="tag">Rating</span>
          <h3>Five dimensions, one act</h3>
          <p>Andi rates once. BAP splits into Trade ratings (PROVIDER, ITEM) and Logistics ratings (FULFILLMENT, PACKAGE_CONDITION, AGENT_BEHAVIOUR).</p>
          <ul><li>/rate</li><li>5 dimensions</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase">
          <span class="num">16</span>
          <span class="tag">Trade · reconcile</span>
          <h3>Money, with proof</h3>
          <p>BAP previews then commits. The <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;">/on_reconcile</code> carries PPN remittance, platform fee, and bukti potong references.</p>
          <ul><li>/reconcile</li><li>PPN · NTPN</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase logi">
          <span class="num">17</span>
          <span class="tag">Logistics · reconcile</span>
          <h3>Batched monthly</h3>
          <p>Per-shipment reconcile doesn't scale at marketplace volume — Logistics settles in monthly batches with <code style="font-family:JetBrains Mono,monospace;font-size:12px;color:var(--logi);">isBatch=true</code>, including FWA rebates and weight-dispute adjustments.</p>
          <ul><li>isBatch</li><li>FWA rebate</li><li>weight adj.</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="phase pay">
          <span class="num">18</span>
          <span class="tag">Payment · reconcile</span>
          <h3>PSP economics</h3>
          <p>Payment BPPs settle their own economics with the BAP — MDR, refund-rate adjustments, authorisation-success-rate reporting — keeping payment health observable network-side.</p>
          <ul><li>MDR</li><li>refund-rate</li><li>auth-rate</li></ul>
        </article>

        <article class="keynote">
          <b>One identifier, three sectors.</b>
          <span style="color:var(--text-2);font-size:14px;">The Payment and Logistics contracts both attach</span>
          <code>linkedContractId</code>
          <span style="color:var(--text-2);font-size:14px;">pointing at the Trade contract. That single field is what lets the BAP — or any auditor — stitch </span>
          <code class="t">TRADE/…/A1F2</code>
          <code class="p">PAY/…/G7H8</code>
          <code class="l">LOG/…/J7K9</code>
          <span style="color:var(--text-2);font-size:14px;">into one coherent transaction story.</span>
        </article>

      </div>
    </section>

